<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">How Ratings Change</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 The Core Formula</p>
  <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Your rating change depends on <span class="text-white font-medium">the difference between your rating and your opponent's</span>. Beat someone rated 200 points above you? Big gain. Lose to someone 200 below? Big loss. The system expects higher-rated players to win.</p>
</div>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Win vs higher-rated:</span> Maximum point gain. If you're rated 1000 and beat a 1300 player, you might gain 20-30 rating points because you outperformed expectations.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Win vs lower-rated:</span> Minimal point gain. Beating a player rated 300 below you only gains 3-5 points — the system expected you to win.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Lose vs higher-rated:</span> Small loss. Losing to someone expected to beat you only costs 3-5 points.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Lose vs lower-rated:</span> Maximum point loss. This is the "upset tax" — losing to weaker opponents is punished heavily (15-25 points).</p>
  </div>
</div>

